 it provides only a very rough estimate or a lower limit on the size of the\nbroad line region. We find that the average mass of the central black holes in\nblazars is ~2.8e8 Msun, with a large dispersion, comparable to those computed\nfor other radio-loud active galactic nuclei.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Jun 2005 15:14:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 1 Aug 2005 15:58:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
